<h2>Approach</h2>
<p>The approach to annotating one citation is as follow:</p>
<form class="well">
<ol>
<b>Determining the Classification</b>
<li>Is there any explicit weakness? Yes (Go to step 2) / No (Go to step 3)</li>
<li>Annotate as <code>Weak</code>. (Go to step 21)</li>
<li>Is there any explicit statement that the author work is <b>based</b> on the cited paper? Yes (Go to step 4) / No (Go to step 5)</li>
<li>Annotate as <code>PBas</code>. (Go to step 21)
<li>Is there any explicit statement about the author <b>using</b> any data/algorithms/definitions in the cited paper? Yes (Go to step 8) / No (Go to step 6)</li>
<li>Is there any explicit statement about the author <b>adapts or modifies</b> any data/algorithms in the cited paper? Yes (Go to step 8) / No (Go to step 7)</li>
<li>Is there any explicit statement about the author uses the cited paper as a <b>motivation</b>? Yes (Go to step 8) / No (Go to step 9)</li>
<li>Annotate as <code>PUse</code> (from step 5) / <code>PModi</code> (from step 6) / <code>PMot</code> (from step 7). (Go to step 21)</li>
<li>Is there any explicit <b>compare and contrast</b> between the work in the citing paper and the cited paper? Yes (Go to step 10) / No (Go to step 13)</li>
<li>Is the compare and contrast <b>negative</b>? Yes (Go to step 11) / No (Go to step 12)</li>
<li>Annotate as <code>CoCoR-</code>. (Go to step 21)</li>
<li>Is the compare and contrast is related to their <b>goals and methods</b>? Yes (Go to step 13) / No (Go to step 14)</li>
<li>Annotate as <code>CoCoR0</code> (Go to step 21)</li>
<li>Annotate as <code>CoCoGM</code>. (Go to step 21)</li>
<li>Is there any explicit statement about <b>similarity</b> with cited paper? Yes (Go to step 17) / No (Go to step 16)</li>
<li>Is there any explicit statement about the author <b>supporting</b> the cited paper? Yes (Go to step 17) / No (Go to step 18)</li>
<li>Annotate as <code>PSim</code> (from step 15) / <code>PSup</code> (from step 16). (Go to step 21)</li>
<li>Is there any explicit statement about the author <b>contrasting two works</b> not related to the citing paper? Yes (Go to step 19) / No (Go to step 20)</li>
<li>Annotate as <code>CoCoXY</code>. (Go to step 21)</li>
<li>Annotate as <code>Neut</code>. (Go to step 21)</li>

<b>Determining the Type</b>
<li>Can the type of citation determined? Yes (Go to step 23) / No (Go to step 22).
<li>Annotate as <code>?</code>(Represents Undetermined). (Go to step 26)
<li>Is the citation Specific? Yes (Go to step 25) / No (Go to step 24)
<li>Annotate as <code>-</code>(Represents General). (Go to step 26)
<li>Annotate as Specific(See #). Go to step 26.
<li>End.
</ol>
